{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.14",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 14 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:1",
      "text": "“Man that is born of a woman is of few days, and full of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:2",
      "text": "He comes forth like a flower, and withers; he flees like a shadow, and continues not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:3",
      "text": "And dost thou open thy eyes upon such a one and bring him into judgment with thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:4",
      "text": "Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean? There is not one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:5",
      "text": "Since his days are determined, and the number of his months is with thee, and thou hast appointed his bounds that he cannot pass,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:6",
      "text": "look away from him, and desist, that he may enjoy, like a hireling, his day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:7",
      "text": "“For there is hope for a tree, if it be cut down, that it will sprout again, and that its shoots will not cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:8",
      "text": "Though its root grow old in the earth, and its stump die in the ground,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:9",
      "text": "yet at the scent of water it will bud and put forth branches like a young plant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:10",
      "text": "But man dies, and is laid low; man breathes his last, and where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:11",
      "text": "As waters fail from a lake, and a river wastes away and dries up,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:12",
      "text": "so man lies down and rises not again; till the heavens are no more he will not awake, or be roused out of his sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:13",
      "text": "Oh that thou wouldest hide me in Sheol, that thou wouldest conceal me until thy wrath be past, that thou wouldest appoint me a set time, and remember me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:14",
      "text": "If a man die, shall he live again? All the days of my service I would wait, till my release should come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:15",
      "text": "Thou wouldest call, and I would answer thee; thou wouldest long for the work of thy hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:16",
      "text": "For then thou wouldest number my steps, thou wouldest not keep watch over my sin;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:17",
      "text": "my transgression would be sealed up in a bag, and thou wouldest cover over my iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:18",
      "text": "“But the mountain falls and crumbles away, and the rock is removed from its place;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:19",
      "text": "the waters wear away the stones; the torrents wash away the soil of the earth; so thou destroyest the hope of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:20",
      "text": "Thou prevailest for ever against him, and he passes; thou changest his countenance, and sendest him away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:21",
      "text": "His sons come to honor, and he does not know it; they are brought low, and he perceives it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.14.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:22",
      "text": "He feels only the pain of his own body, and he mourns only for himself.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
